snippet: German teenager Alexander Zverev won his first ATP Tour singles title with a 6-2 3-6 7-5 upset win over Switzerland's world number three Stan Wawrinka at the St Petersburg Open on Sunday....
lead_paragraph: German teenager Alexander Zverev won his first ATP Tour singles title with a 6-2 3-6 7-5 upset win over Switzerland's world number three Stan Wawrinka at the St Petersburg Open on Sunday.

headline.print_headline: Zverev Shocks Wawrinka to Win St Petersburg Open
headline.main: Zverev Shocks Wawrinka to Win St Petersburg Open
